{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:59:12.826472+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a complete walkthrough of the database migrations in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThere are **3 migration SQL files** currently in the `migrations/` directory, and a `MIGRATION_HISTORY.md` that records **6 total migrations** that have been applied to deployed environments. The last three (004–006) were historically applied but their files have been archived out of the active directory (the history file notes this is expected behavior).\n\n---\n\n## Migrations in Order\n\n### 1. `001_create_users.sql` — *applied 2024-11-04*\n**Creates the foundational `users` table.**\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE users (\n    id           BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n    email        TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,\n    display_name TEXT,\n    created_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n- `id` is an auto-incrementing 64-bit integer primary key.\n- `email` is unique and required.\n- `display_name` is optional.\n- `created_at` defaults to the current timestamp.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `002_create_sessions.sql` — *applied 2024-12-10*\n**Creates the `sessions` table with a foreign key to `users`.**\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE sessions (\n    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY,\n    user_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    issued_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    expires_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL\n);\n```\n\n- Sessions use a UUID primary key (rather than a sequential integer).\n- `user_id` is a foreign key to `users.id` with `ON DELETE CASCADE` — deleting a user automatically deletes all their sessions.\n- Tracks `issued_at` (defaults to now) and `expires_at` (must be explicitly set).\n\n---\n\n### 3. `003_add_session_index.sql` — *applied 2025-01-22*\n**Adds an index on `sessions.user_id` for faster lookups.**\n\n```sql\nCREATE INDEX idx_sessions_user_id ON sessions(user_id);\n```\n\n- Improves query performance for joins and lookups that filter or group by `user_id` (e.g., \"find all sessions for a given user\").\n\n---\n\n### 4–6. Historically Applied (Archived)\n\nThe `MIGRATION_HISTORY.md` records three additional migrations that were run in production but whose files have been moved out of the active `migrations/` directory:\n\n| # | File | Date | What it does |\n|---|------|------|-------------|\n| 004 | `004_partition_users.sql` | 2025-02-18 | Range-partitions the `users` table by `created_at` (monthly intervals). |\n| 005 | `005_archive_legacy_sessions.sql` | 2025-03-05 | Moves sessions older than 90 days into a `sessions_archive` table. |\n| 006 | `006_grant_readonly_role.sql` | 2025-04-12 | Creates an `app_readonly` database role with read-only grants. |\n\nThese have been archived (likely to a `migrations/archived/` path that no longer exists in the current tree), but the history file is considered authoritative for audit/on-call purposes.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe current active schema, after all migrations, would be:\n\n- **`users`** — stores user accounts (optionally range-partitioned monthly by `created_at`).\n- **`sessions`** — stores session tokens linked to users via FK, with an index on `user_id` for fast lookups.\n- **`sessions_archive`** — stores sessions older than 90 days (populated by a periodic archival process).\n- An **`app_readonly`** database role with read-only access.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 957, "prompt_tokens": 5197, "total_tokens": 6154, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 107, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 4544}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "7d4a09c52cc042d2a14e74ffc64b417d", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead89-7a04-7ca